Thief Nora: There's a strong beastly smell... It's up
ahead.
Clea: Specifically, what should we do?

Mage Relm: It's certain that magic is involved, but how to
turn them back into humans...

it.

Clea: Stasis-san! We've come to defeat the werewolves as

Clea: Here I come, let's go!

Mage Relm: I don't know the cause! It's certain that
transformation magic and nightmare magic are involved.

Mage Relm: But it's surpassing the limits of transformation
magic! We might have to bring them to the Magic Academy.

Priestess Sophia: I have something I want to try. I want to
attempt a treatment to restore the goat-san back to normal.
Clea: Alright, is there anything we can do?

Priestess Sophia: If possible, I want everyone to stay
away, and as a precaution, please talk to the goat-san.

Priestess Sophia: Hehe, as the shrine maiden also
mentioned, a priestess is someone who brings salvation
through healing.
Priestess Sophia: So, please leave this to me.
Clea: Understood, leave it to me.

Clea: However, please make sure not to die under any
circumstances.
Priestess Sophia: Yes, I will definitely save him.

Priestess Sophia: Goddess Imiserinos, grant a warm embrace
to the wounded.

Priestess Sophia (If I can recall the feeling of the
healing I did with Eleo-chan, it should definitely go well)

Priestess Sophia (Even without Eleo-chan, I will make sure
to succeed!)
Priestess Sophia: No... it hasn't returned to normal...!?

Priestess Sophia: I have no intention of hurting you. I
want to save you, can you believe me?

Priestess Sophia (What can I do to completely dispel her
guardedness that words alone cannot reach...)

Priestess Sophia (In the mythological era, the goddess
Deiree sealed the demons with her own body...)

Priestess Sophia: Although the goddess I believe in may be
different, I am prepared for this!
Would you like to skip the adult scene?

Mage Stasis: I never thought I would be a werewolf...
Perhaps you, I, and I are a warning to each other.

Mage Stasis: Thank you very much for helping me. I
apologize for not having any memories...

Priestess Sophia: It's good to be back to normal. I hope
nothing similar happens in the future.
Mage Stasis: I somehow feel like everything will be okay.

Mage Stasis: This place... more precisely, it's from a
place further away.

Mage Stasis: When I was young, I used to come here often
with my mother. She would always say, 'Someday, we will live
in a big, big building.'
Priestess Sophia: I see, I didn't know that.

Mage Stasis: The castle my mother wanted to live in was in
ruins, and to her, I was nothing more than a nuisance.

Mage Stasis: I have finally been able to accept it. The
monster that was the feelings towards my mother that existed
within me has disappeared.
Priestess Sophia: Yes, the problem has been resolved.

Goat of the Bulk Gang: Don't worry, Stasis! The next time
you turn into a werewolf and go on a rampage, I'll make sure
to kill you properly!
Mage Stasis: Ahaha... Please go easy on me.

Priestess Sophia: Now, let's meet up with Nora-chan and
Relm-chan.
